  "prompt": "What integer solutions to x and y are there for 167x+113y=1?",
  "response": "To solve the Diophantine equation \\( 167x + 113y = 1 \\) for integer solutions \\( x \\) and \\( y \\), we'll use the **Extended Euclidean Algorithm**. This algorithm not only finds the greatest common divisor (gcd) of two integers but also expresses the gcd as a linear combination of those integers.\n\n### Step 1: Apply the Euclidean Algorithm\nFirst, determine the gcd of 167 and 113 to ensure that the equation has integer solutions.\n\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n167 &= 1 \\times 113 + 54 \\\\\n113 &= 2 \\times 54 + 5 \\\\\n54 &= 10 \\times 5 + 4 \\\\\n5 &= 1 \\times 4 + 1 \\\\\n4 &= 4 \\times 1 + 0 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\n\nThe gcd is the last non-zero remainder, which is **1**. Since the gcd divides the right-hand side of the equation (which is also 1), integer solutions exist.\n\n### Step 2: Back-Substitute to Find Particular Solutions\nWe'll express 1 as a combination of 167 and 113 by back-substituting the remainders:\n\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n1 &= 5 - 1 \\times 4 \\\\\n&= 5 - 1 \\times (54 - 10 \\times 5) \\\\\n&= 11 \\times 5 - 1 \\times 54 \\\\\n&= 11 \\times (113 - 2 \\times 54) - 23 \\times 54 \\\\\n&= 34 \\times 113 - 23 \\times 167 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\n\nThis gives us a particular solution:\n\\[\nx_0 = -23, \\quad y_0 = 34\n\\]\n\n### Step 3: Generalize the Solution\nThe general solution incorporates all possible integer values by introducing a parameter \\( t \\):\n\n\\[\n\\begin{cases}\nx = x_0 + \\frac{113}{\\gcd(167,113)} \\times t = -23 + 113t \\\\\ny = y_0 - \\frac{167}{\\gcd(167,113)} \\times t = 34 - 167t \\\\\n\\end{cases}\n\\]\n\nSince \\( \\gcd(167,113) = 1 \\), the solutions simplify to:\n\n\\[\nx = -23 + 113t \\\\\ny = 34 - 167t \\\\\n\\]\n\nwhere \\( t \\) is any integer.\n\n### Conclusion\nAll integer solutions to the equation \\( 167x + 113y = 1 \\) are given by:\n\n\\[\nx = -23 + 113t \\\\\ny = 34 - 167t \\\\\n\\]\n\nfor any integer \\( t \\).\n\n**Final Answer:**\nAll integer solutions are given by x = \u201323\u202f+\u202f113\u00b7k and y =\u00a034\u00a0\u2013\u00a0167\u00b7k for some integer k. Thus,\n\nx = \u221223 + 113k,\ny =\u00a034 \u2212 167k",
